  "name": "Wavefold Abyss",
  "mood": "Aether",
  "engines": [
    "Obrix"
  ],
  "description": "Saw into Wavefolder (proc1) at maximum possible gain routing — the fold point deep enough to generate 7+ harmonics — then HP (proc2) at 400 Hz strips the fundamental, leaving only the folded upper partials. What remains is not a traditional synth sound but a crystalline overtone cloud: aggressive without being brash, complex without being cacophonous. Mono for maximum edge. proc2Feedback 0.35 adds a controlled metallic rattle to the HP stage. LFO→proc1Cutoff at 0.09 Hz makes the fold depth breathe over 11-second cycles.",
